00:58:05,814 --> 00:58:08,450
We'll play our beat now.

1563
00:58:08,517 --> 00:58:09,985
We created a beat

1564
00:58:10,052 --> 00:58:13,555
that could send a message
with a bright and positive energy

1565
00:58:13,622 --> 00:58:15,357
instead of something dark.

1566
00:58:15,424 --> 00:58:16,758
The title

1567
00:58:16,825 --> 00:58:18,894
is 'Ssak' like "saessak" meaning sprout.

1568
00:58:18,961 --> 00:58:20,495
EXCITED
'Ssak.'

1569
00:58:20,562 --> 00:58:21,563
It can also mean "everything."

1570
00:58:21,630 --> 00:58:23,365
ALSO MEANING THEY'LL SWEEP EVERYTHING UP
Like, "We'll sweep everything up."

1571
00:58:25,334 --> 00:58:26,835
"Sweep everything up."
That's awesome.

1572
00:58:26,902 --> 00:58:29,271
And we could say
that you're all "sprouts" on this show.

1573
00:58:29,338 --> 00:58:30,539
FIRST TIME ON SHOW ME THE MONEY
Right, in a way.

1574
00:58:30,606 --> 00:58:31,973
I'm so excited for this.

1575
00:58:32,040 --> 00:58:32,974
Let's start.

1576
00:58:33,041 --> 00:58:34,109
What will it be like?

1577
00:58:34,176 --> 00:58:35,377
Hit songs...

1578
00:58:35,444 --> 00:58:37,179
Hip-hop that the public would love.

1579
00:58:37,246 --> 00:58:39,414
They're great at making songs like that.

1580
00:58:39,481 --> 00:58:40,949
I'm pretty excited.

1581
00:58:41,450 --> 00:58:44,286
TEAM GRAY X LOCO'S BEAT
IS FINALLY REVEALED

1582
00:58:47,156 --> 00:58:49,191
EMBARRASSED

1583
00:58:51,193 --> 00:58:54,997
LOCO DOES A GUIDE
TO HELP UNDERSTAND THE BEAT

1584
00:58:59,334 --> 00:59:02,104
THE MEMBERS LOVE IT

1585
00:59:02,171 --> 00:59:03,105
STOP!

1586
00:59:09,611 --> 00:59:11,079
VERY SATISFIED

1587
00:59:11,146 --> 00:59:12,815
CORAY, CORAY!

1588
00:59:13,882 --> 00:59:15,951
It's so great.
Ear worm, you know.

1589
00:59:16,018 --> 00:59:17,886
Ssak, ssak, ssak, ssak

1590
00:59:17,953 --> 00:59:18,854
It was great.

1591
00:59:18,921 --> 00:59:21,022
It's the first time
doing a song like that.

1592
00:59:21,089 --> 00:59:22,824
But I love that it has a bright energy.

1593
00:59:22,891 --> 00:59:24,025
I feel like

1594
00:59:24,092 --> 00:59:25,360
it's a song that people

1595
00:59:25,427 --> 00:59:26,595
can automatically sing along to.

1596
00:59:26,662 --> 00:59:27,796
So I love it.

1597
00:59:27,863 --> 00:59:30,132
Do you think you'll come up
with good verses?

1598
00:59:30,199 --> 00:59:33,435
I've never done a song

1599
00:59:33,502 --> 00:59:34,770
with this format before.

1600
00:59:34,837 --> 00:59:36,338
But the reason I came here

1601
00:59:36,405 --> 00:59:38,774
was to break past my limit

1602
00:59:38,841 --> 00:59:40,575
and challenge myself to new things,

1603
00:59:40,642 --> 00:59:42,878
so I'd like to try it.

1604
00:59:43,512 --> 00:59:47,449
I actually think it's kind of hard

1605
00:59:47,516 --> 00:59:49,551
to imagine some of you performing this,

1606
00:59:49,618 --> 00:59:53,188
because I think it's different
from the kind of music you did so far.

1607
00:59:53,255 --> 00:59:57,392
But I think that's why
the song is more charming.

1608
00:59:58,327 --> 01:00:01,663
I'm honestly a bit worried
about how the five of us

1609
01:00:01,730 --> 01:00:04,499
will blend together for this song,
since everyone's so different.

1610
01:00:04,566 --> 01:00:06,201
But I have faith in our team.

1611
01:00:06,268 --> 01:00:07,602
I'm sure we'll make a great song.

1612
01:00:07,669 --> 01:00:11,106
I think it's pretty special
that we became a team, so...

1613
01:00:11,740 --> 01:00:12,607
We prepared a gift.

1614
01:00:12,674 --> 01:00:13,742
A little gift.

1615
01:00:15,344 --> 01:00:17,145
WHAT PRESENT DID GRAY AND LOCO PREPARE?
What?

1616
01:00:17,212 --> 01:00:17,946
Grills.

1617
01:00:18,013 --> 01:00:19,648
GROUP GRILLS

1618
01:00:19,715 --> 01:00:21,216
Thank you. Thank you.

1619
01:00:21,283 --> 01:00:22,617
We'll be great teammates.

1620
01:00:22,684 --> 01:00:23,519
Wow.

1621
01:00:24,987 --> 01:00:27,823
Grills are pretty cool accessories.

1622
01:00:27,890 --> 01:00:29,458
POPULAR ACCESSORY AMONG HIP-HOP ARTISTS
They're like earrings.

1623
01:00:29,525 --> 01:00:31,393
They gave us something
that would make us look cool.

1624
01:00:31,460 --> 01:00:32,194
I'm so happy.

1625
01:00:32,261 --> 01:00:34,062
I'm going to wear it
even when I'm meeting my mom.

1626
01:00:34,129 --> 01:00:35,297
Thank you.

1627
01:00:35,364 --> 01:00:37,399
Since this is a team mission,

1628
01:00:37,466 --> 01:00:39,968
I wanted us to become a real team.

1629
01:00:40,035 --> 01:00:41,670
It was a gift to show that.

1630
01:00:42,804 --> 01:00:43,839
TEAM GRAY X LOCO
MAKING MOLDS FOR THE GRILLS

1631
01:00:43,906 --> 01:00:44,973
You look cute right now.

1632
01:00:47,309 --> 01:00:49,845
MEMORY OF GRILLS TAKEN BY LOCO

1633
01:00:51,280 --> 01:00:54,683
MEMORY OF GRILLS TAKEN BY GRAY

1634
01:00:54,750 --> 01:00:58,587
It feels like we've already
grown quite close.

1635
01:00:58,654 --> 01:01:01,790
It's our first mission as a team,

1636
01:01:01,857 --> 01:01:04,759
so we thought we should gather often

1637
01:01:04,826 --> 01:01:08,597
and practice together and grow closer.

1638
01:01:08,664 --> 01:01:09,764
We have to help them

1639
01:01:09,831 --> 01:01:12,133
in any way we can.

1640
01:01:12,200 --> 01:01:13,235
BUGAHYEON-DONG PRACTICE ROOM

1641
01:01:13,302 --> 01:01:14,069
TEAM GRAY X LOCO'S FIRST DAY OF PRACTICE

1642
01:01:14,136 --> 01:01:14,936
How have you been?

1643
01:01:15,003 --> 01:01:17,105
We haven't planned the formations yet,

1644
01:01:17,172 --> 01:01:18,773
so let's just get a hang of this first.

1645
01:01:18,840 --> 01:01:21,810
MASON HOME will sing
the hook at the beginning.

1646
01:01:21,877 --> 01:01:23,679
Let's just try it out for now.

1647
01:01:24,947 --> 01:01:28,450
HOW WILL THEIR FIRST PRACTICE GO?

1648
01:01:28,517 --> 01:01:31,520
I should show them soon

1649
01:01:31,587 --> 01:01:34,322
MASON HOME STARTS SMOOTHLY
You'll hear me everywhere

1650
01:01:34,389 --> 01:01:37,225
Ssak, ssak, sweep up everything

1651
01:01:37,292 --> 01:01:39,694
OXYNOVA'S TURN NEXT
Ssak, ssak, sweep up everything

1652
01:01:39,761 --> 01:01:41,396
I see things through to the end

1653
01:01:41,463 --> 01:01:42,964
OXYNOVA ALSO DOES HIS PART SMOOTHLY
Look at me, my life's sweet

1654
01:01:45,167 --> 01:01:47,769
MASON HOME DOES HIS PART WELL

1655
01:01:47,836 --> 01:01:50,338
I was pretty surprised
at MASON HOME's verse.

1656
01:01:50,405 --> 01:01:53,975
He designed the melodic parts really well.

1657
01:01:54,042 --> 01:01:55,710
It suited the beat.

1658
01:01:59,514 --> 01:02:01,416
They all came up with verses

1659
01:02:01,483 --> 01:02:03,485
that expressed themselves well.

1660
01:02:03,552 --> 01:02:04,419
It was good.

1661
01:02:05,754 --> 01:02:08,690
OSUN ALSO ENDS SMOOTHLY

1662
01:02:08,757 --> 01:02:11,727
TEAM GRAY X LOCO
FINISH THEIR FIRST PRACTICE WELL

1663
01:02:12,961 --> 01:02:14,729
MASON HOME, you're going first,

1664
01:02:14,796 --> 01:02:17,732
but you keep habitually
looking 45 degrees down

1665
01:02:17,799 --> 01:02:20,001
while you're rapping.

1666
01:02:20,068 --> 01:02:22,837
I should show them soon

1667
01:02:22,904 --> 01:02:25,774
LOOKING DOWN WHILE RAPPING
You'll hear me everywhere

1668
01:02:25,841 --> 01:02:28,310
This time, why don't you

1669
01:02:28,377 --> 01:02:31,780
GIVING ADVICE ABOUT HIS GAZE
try to look forward?

1670
01:02:31,847 --> 01:02:34,215
You have a very important role.

1671
01:02:34,282 --> 01:02:35,784
You're doing the first hook.

1672
01:02:35,851 --> 01:02:37,452
We want you to lead the performance.

1673
01:02:37,519 --> 01:02:38,687
I'll do my best.

1674
01:02:38,754 --> 01:02:40,121
I have to make
a strong opening

1675
01:02:40,188 --> 01:02:43,658
