01:46:21,841 --> 01:46:23,108
They were amazing.

2842
01:46:23,175 --> 01:46:24,110
GREAT JOB

2843
01:46:25,544 --> 01:46:27,313
I feel like the performance
ended so quickly.

2844
01:46:27,380 --> 01:46:28,514
Yeah.

2845
01:46:28,581 --> 01:46:31,350
That's actually
what's charming about it.

2846
01:46:31,417 --> 01:46:32,418
The urgency.

2847
01:46:32,485 --> 01:46:34,453
The hook is catchy too.

2848
01:46:34,520 --> 01:46:35,588
TICK TOCK

2849
01:46:37,290 --> 01:46:39,758
ZICO, CRUSH, what did you think?

2850
01:46:39,825 --> 01:46:41,460
First of all,

2851
01:46:41,527 --> 01:46:45,965
everyone put so much effort into this,

2852
01:46:46,032 --> 01:46:50,102
so I was happy that their energy
reached all of us.

2853
01:46:50,169 --> 01:46:51,337
It feels like I performed with them.

2854
01:46:51,404 --> 01:46:52,371
Yeah.

2855
01:46:52,438 --> 01:46:54,440
I couldn't control my excitement.

2856
01:46:55,808 --> 01:46:57,376
ALREADY STANDING SINCE THE BEGINNING

2857
01:46:57,443 --> 01:46:58,477
IN SYNC WITH THE MEMBERS
Tick Tock, time's flowing

2858
01:46:58,544 --> 01:47:00,379
Scrolling Insta, brain fried

2859
01:47:00,446 --> 01:47:01,480
IN SYNC
Big talk, you're talking too much

2860
01:47:01,547 --> 01:47:04,650
FROM DOUBLING
Turn the club up, turn the club up

2861
01:47:04,717 --> 01:47:05,951
TO THE GESTURES
Hallelu

2862
01:47:06,018 --> 01:47:08,354
PERFECT TEAMWORK
Swiper no swiping, swiper no swiping

2863
01:47:08,421 --> 01:47:09,922
Team ZIC,

2864
01:47:09,989 --> 01:47:11,490
you all did a great job.

2865
01:47:11,557 --> 01:47:15,828
ZICO and I were really ambitious

2866
01:47:15,895 --> 01:47:19,698
so practice must have been pretty tough,

2867
01:47:19,765 --> 01:47:21,667
but I feel like

2868
01:47:21,734 --> 01:47:23,802
you overcame your limits

2869
01:47:23,869 --> 01:47:25,604
on stage this time

2870
01:47:25,671 --> 01:47:28,374
during the performance,

2871
01:47:28,441 --> 01:47:30,643
so I'm really proud and grateful.

2872
01:47:30,710 --> 01:47:32,177
You did a really great job.

2873
01:47:32,244 --> 01:47:33,412
Thank you.

2874
01:47:33,479 --> 01:47:34,980
ZIC! ZIC!

2875
01:47:35,047 --> 01:47:36,615
I can tell they practiced a lot.

2876
01:47:36,682 --> 01:47:37,916
Yeah.

2877
01:47:37,983 --> 01:47:39,184
Great job.

2878
01:47:39,251 --> 01:47:39,918
Good job.

2879
01:47:39,985 --> 01:47:41,287
Great job, guys.

2880
01:47:41,354 --> 01:47:42,154
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2881
01:47:42,221 --> 01:47:43,122
Thank you.

2882
01:47:46,292 --> 01:47:47,092
I loved the details.

2883
01:47:47,159 --> 01:47:47,926
I'm relieved.

2884
01:47:47,993 --> 01:47:49,061
They all had
the same amount of time,

2885
01:47:49,128 --> 01:47:52,865
but the vibe's so different for each team.

2886
01:47:54,834 --> 01:47:56,135
- That was fun.
- It's finally over.

2887
01:47:56,202 --> 01:47:58,771
It's over now.

2888
01:47:58,838 --> 01:47:59,972
- I want to do it again.
- Right?

2889
01:48:00,039 --> 01:48:00,639
I want to do it again.

2890
01:48:00,706 --> 01:48:02,574
I put in
even more energy this time.

2891
01:48:02,641 --> 01:48:04,276
I think we were born
to be on stage.

2892
01:48:04,343 --> 01:48:05,644
Our team's the best.

2893
01:48:06,746 --> 01:48:07,713
I feel amazing.

2894
01:48:07,780 --> 01:48:08,881
I'm so happy.

2895
01:48:08,948 --> 01:48:10,949
I think we really crushed it.

2896
01:48:11,016 --> 01:48:14,019
I feel so relieved it's over,
and I'm proud of my team.

2897
01:48:14,086 --> 01:48:16,155
ZICO and CRUSH were a great help.

2898
01:48:16,222 --> 01:48:17,556
Are you nervous?
You're okay, right?

2899
01:48:17,623 --> 01:48:19,158
MOM MODE
Are you okay?

2900
01:48:20,159 --> 01:48:22,461
It felt so reassuring
to have them on our team.

2901
01:48:23,195 --> 01:48:25,497
I can't do this.
They all did great.

2902
01:48:25,564 --> 01:48:26,932
ZICO X CRUSH ARE LOST IN THOUGHT
ABOUT THE ELIMINATION

2903
01:48:26,999 --> 01:48:27,600
What do we do?

2904
01:48:29,969 --> 01:48:33,472
Honestly, I could say it was flawless.

2905
01:48:33,539 --> 01:48:34,673
They were so good.

2906
01:48:34,740 --> 01:48:37,676
- Yeah, no one disappointed.
- No one.

2907
01:48:37,743 --> 01:48:41,013
I feel so bad.

2908
01:48:41,080 --> 01:48:41,914
For real.

2909
01:48:43,416 --> 01:48:45,250
And I grew so close to them.

2910
01:48:45,317 --> 01:48:47,953
Honestly, I think
every single one of them did great.

2911
01:48:48,020 --> 01:48:49,722
We were a bit worried,

2912
01:48:49,789 --> 01:48:55,027
but someone who completely
wiped away our concerns

2913
01:48:55,094 --> 01:48:58,063
and surprised us was Marv.

2914
01:48:58,130 --> 01:49:00,299
So I'm really lost right now.

2915
01:49:03,436 --> 01:49:05,738
It'll be tough for this team.

2916
01:49:05,805 --> 01:49:07,673
Yeah...

2917
01:49:09,608 --> 01:49:11,477
We grew so close

2918
01:49:11,544 --> 01:49:13,512
in a short amount of time,

2919
01:49:13,579 --> 01:49:17,149
so it was difficult to make our decision.

2920
01:49:17,216 --> 01:49:19,151
That's why it took so long.

2921
01:49:19,218 --> 01:49:22,287
During that brief period of time,

2922
01:49:22,354 --> 01:49:24,923
all the times we spent together

2923
01:49:24,990 --> 01:49:26,592
became good memories.

2924
01:49:26,659 --> 01:49:28,961
I could feel that today.

2925
01:49:29,028 --> 01:49:31,196
I'm really grateful
you all joined our team,

2926
01:49:31,263 --> 01:49:33,799
and I'm grateful that you made us proud

2927
01:49:33,866 --> 01:49:36,602
with such an amazing performance.

2928
01:49:36,669 --> 01:49:38,303
Thank you.

2929
01:49:38,370 --> 01:49:41,173
TIME FOR THE ELIMINATION
Please announce the eliminated member.

2930
01:49:41,240 --> 01:49:44,376
I thought I'd end up talking gibberish,

2931
01:49:44,443 --> 01:49:46,278
so I wrote it down.

2932
01:49:46,345 --> 01:49:50,349
We really couldn't find a reason
for anyone to be eliminated.

2933
01:49:50,416 --> 01:49:53,886
That's how flawless
your performance was today.

2934
01:49:53,953 --> 01:49:56,221
That's why our decision

2935
01:49:56,288 --> 01:49:59,158
was made not based on
who needed improvement,

2936
01:49:59,225 --> 01:50:01,994
but on who would be able

2937
01:50:02,061 --> 01:50:04,596
to show synergy with us

2938
01:50:04,663 --> 01:50:07,466
in the long run

2939
01:50:07,533 --> 01:50:10,035
for the remaining

2940
01:50:10,102 --> 01:50:12,171
missions and the main stage.

2941
01:50:12,238 --> 01:50:14,206
We had to set new standards.

2942
01:50:14,273 --> 01:50:17,709
So as a result, we had to choose

2943
01:50:17,776 --> 01:50:20,446
the member who came to mind last.

2944
01:50:22,848 --> 01:50:26,185
The eliminated member is...

2945
01:50:26,252 --> 01:50:30,356
TO BE CONTINUED SHORTLY

2946
01:50:30,956 --> 01:50:34,660
The eliminated member is...

2947
01:50:40,566 --> 01:50:43,702
WHO WILL BE ELIMINATED
FROM TEAM ZICO X CRUSH?

2948
01:50:46,038 --> 01:50:47,072
NOSUN.

2949
01:50:47,139 --> 01:50:48,073
NOSUN.

2950
01:50:48,140 --> 01:50:50,542
NOSUN IS ELIMINATED

2951
01:50:55,648 --> 01:50:57,850
I do understand their decision

2952
01:50:57,917 --> 01:50:59,518
because they probably have

2953
01:50:59,585 --> 01:51:01,753
a clear image in mind for their team.

2954
01:51:01,820 --> 01:51:04,289
- It must've been hard to decide.
- Yeah.

2955
01:51:04,356 --> 01:51:05,324
Right...

2956
01:51:09,962 --> 01:51:13,799
I think I've grown a lot
through my experience here

2957
01:51:13,866 --> 01:51:15,734
at SHOW ME THE MONEY 12.

2958
01:51:15,801 --> 01:51:19,838
I was able to make a great performance
with my teammates,

2959
01:51:19,905 --> 01:51:22,374
so I don't have any regrets.

2960
01:51:22,441 --> 01:51:24,710
I've always said this,

2961
01:51:24,777 --> 01:51:28,113
but if I've done my best...

2962
01:51:28,180 --> 01:51:29,515
That's life.

2963
01:51:29,582 --> 01:51:33,585
So I'll be able to leave with no regrets.

2964
01:51:33,652 --> 01:51:35,821
Yes, sir. And I'm really grateful
toward our producers.

2965
01:51:35,888 --> 01:51:37,389
Thank you, NOSUN.

2966
01:51:37,456 --> 01:51:39,024
- Thank you.
- NOSUN, thank you.

2967
01:51:39,091 --> 01:51:40,425
- Yes, sir. Yes, sir. Thank you.
- You did a great job.

2968
01:51:40,492 --> 01:51:41,360
Thank you.

2969
01:51:41,427 --> 01:51:43,495
You did great.

2970
01:51:47,833 --> 01:51:49,701
I do feel pretty sad.

2971
01:51:49,768 --> 01:51:52,938
But I'm glad the younger members survived.

2972
01:51:53,005 --> 01:51:54,606
It was a great experience

2973
01:51:54,673 --> 01:51:56,108
and I learned a lot.

2974
01:51:56,175 --> 01:51:57,709
I had a great time with my teammates

2975
01:51:57,776 --> 01:52:00,479
and I learned so much from the producers.

2976
01:52:00,546 --> 01:52:02,114
My love for you.

2977
01:52:02,181 --> 01:52:05,751
I want to thank the viewers

2978
01:52:05,818 --> 01:52:08,820
for showing me love and support until now.

2979
01:52:08,887 --> 01:52:13,425
I don't know when I'll be on TV again,

2980
01:52:13,492 --> 01:52:15,827
but I'll see you again someday.

2981
01:52:15,894 --> 01:52:17,896
People talk
When they see our stage

2982
01:52:20,666 --> 01:52:21,767
Team ZIC's practice...

2983
01:52:21,834 --> 01:52:23,435
Over!

2984
01:52:27,406 --> 01:52:28,540
ZICO X CRUSH: HAON, NOSUN,
RAF SANDOU, MARV, JUNHYUK JUNG

2985
01:52:28,607 --> 01:52:31,243
NOSUN ELIMINATED

2986
01:52:31,310 --> 01:52:35,647
I really liked how diverse
the contestants were.

2987
01:52:35,714 --> 01:52:38,350
The stage quality
was amazing.

2988
01:52:38,417 --> 01:52:39,851
Everyone was perfect.

2989
01:52:39,918 --> 01:52:42,454
It must've been really tough

2990
01:52:42,521 --> 01:52:43,922
